

SecureFile

Overview
    SecureFile is a user-friendly file encryption tool for users using WSL2, featuring both a CLI and GUI for ease of use.

Installation
    Clone the repository:
        ```bash
        git clone https://github.com/yourusername/securefile.git
        cd securefile
        ```

Create a virtual environment:
    ```bash
    python3 -m venv venv
    ```

Activate the virtual environment:
    mac: 
    ```bash
    source venv/bin/activate
    ```
    win: 
    ```bash
    venv\Scripts\activate
    ```

Upgrade pip:
    ```bash
    python3 -m pip install --upgrade pip
    ```

Install dependencies:
    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

Usage:
    Encryption:
    ```bash
    ./securefile.sh encrypt <filename> <password>
    ```

    Decryption:
    ```bash
    ./securefile.sh decrypt <filename> <password>
    ```

Documentation
    This approach focuses on AES encryption, making the implementation simpler and more straightforward while still providing robust encryption capabilities.

Ensure File Permission:
    ```bash
    chmod +x securefile.sh
    chmod +x tests/test_securefile.sh
    ```
